  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ERFS (Emergency Response Fund Scheme) funding is pre-positioned emergency funding designed to be used in immediate first phase emergency response work during sudden onset humanitarian crises.  Important factors to consider when deciding whether to draw down funds include: scale of the crisis, our capacity to respond, leverage for other funding, timing for rapid response (should be immediately/very soon after sudden onset).</narrative>
  </description>
